# Next.js frontend

## App Router

- **Server Components** by default; `"use client"` only when using hooks, Convex, or browser APIs
- Convex hooks (`useQuery`, `useMutation`) only in **client** components
- Route groups: shop pages under `src/app/(shop)/`; shared layout uses `AppProviders`
- Use `next/link` and `next/image` (configure `remotePatterns` in `next.config.ts`)

## Convex client

- Single `ConvexReactClient` in `ConvexClientProvider`; env: `NEXT_PUBLIC_CONVEX_URL`
- Prefer `useQuery(api.module.fn)` for realtime data — avoid duplicating with REST/axios
- Handle loading: `data === undefined` → skeleton/spinner (`Skeleton` from shadcn)

## Data fetching

- Do not fetch large lists in one query from the client; use paginated Convex queries
- Product detail: `useQuery(api.products.getByExternalId, { externalId })`

## Performance

- Dynamic import heavy client-only modules when needed
- `export const dynamic = "force-dynamic"` only where required (shop layout already sets when needed)
